WEBVTT

00:01.069 --> 00:01.202
.

00:06.407 --> 00:07.341
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:07.975 --> 00:08.976
sexually based offenses

00:09.009 --> 00:11.612
are considered
especially heinous.

00:11.645 --> 00:14.248
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:14.282 --> 00:16.150
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:16.184 --> 00:17.418
are members of an elite squad

00:17.451 --> 00:19.520
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:19.553 --> 00:21.422
These are their stories.

00:23.191 --> 00:24.492
- My dad used to have
an expression.

00:24.525 --> 00:27.361
He said, "The greatest sin
any person can commit

00:27.395 --> 00:29.397
is the abuse of power."

00:29.430 --> 00:31.565
And the greatest
abuse of power

00:31.599 --> 00:33.501
was rape.

00:33.534 --> 00:36.170
It takes a woman
a long time to heal.

00:36.204 --> 00:39.073
And when the victim
isn't believed,

00:39.107 --> 00:40.541
when she goes through
the invasive process

00:40.574 --> 00:43.411
of having a rape kit
put together,

00:43.444 --> 00:45.413
and then it's stuck
on a shelf somewhere--

00:45.446 --> 00:49.283
and then the rape kit
is never, ever tested--

00:49.317 --> 00:50.451
we fail.

00:50.484 --> 00:51.619
We fail her.

00:51.652 --> 00:54.288
We fail so many women.

00:54.322 --> 00:57.591
I'm proud to say
today we did not fail.

00:57.625 --> 01:00.528
Thanks to the dedicated
efforts of law enforcement,

01:00.561 --> 01:01.629
the whole legal system,

01:01.662 --> 01:03.464
the victim's advocacy groups,

01:03.497 --> 01:06.134
and particularly my friend here,

01:06.167 --> 01:09.637
Lieutenant Olivia Benson of SVU,

01:09.670 --> 01:10.871
congratulations, Lieutenant.

01:10.904 --> 01:12.173
[applause]

01:12.206 --> 01:14.308
- Thank you.
Thank you.

01:14.342 --> 01:16.344
Mr. Vice President,
we are so honored

01:16.377 --> 01:18.379
to stand here today with you

01:18.412 --> 01:20.481
to announce that in
beginning to clear

01:20.514 --> 01:22.516
the national rape kit backlog,

01:22.550 --> 01:25.153
we have taken rapists
off the streets.

01:25.186 --> 01:26.587
We have prevented future crimes.

01:26.620 --> 01:28.722
We have given victims closure.

01:28.756 --> 01:33.194
And we have also righted
a terrible wrong.

01:33.227 --> 01:35.263
16 years ago,

01:35.296 --> 01:37.298
Sean Roberts was
convicted of a rape

01:37.331 --> 01:40.301
here in New York City
that he did not commit.

01:40.334 --> 01:43.537
By processing an untested
rape kit in Detroit,

01:43.571 --> 01:47.608
we were able to identify
the real rapist

01:47.641 --> 01:49.243
and set Sean free.

01:49.277 --> 01:50.478
[applause]

01:50.511 --> 01:53.514
[camera shutters clicking]

01:55.649 --> 01:58.552
- I want to thank everyone
who tested the kits.

01:58.586 --> 02:00.554
I've only been out
of prison for a month,

02:00.588 --> 02:02.623
but it already feels like
a second chance at life.

02:02.656 --> 02:05.359
I bear no ill will
towards Melanie Harper.

02:05.393 --> 02:07.461
She's as much a victim
as I am in this.

02:07.495 --> 02:09.630
This is a fresh start for me,

02:09.663 --> 02:12.500
Melanie,
and her daughter, Ashley.

02:12.533 --> 02:14.435
- We're looking forward
to the next chapter.

02:14.468 --> 02:16.270
- And my mother and I
want to make amends--

02:16.304 --> 02:17.938
have Sean in our lives.

02:17.971 --> 02:19.240
I'm getting married next month.

02:19.273 --> 02:20.508
I've invited Sean
to the wedding.

02:20.541 --> 02:22.410
- Thank you.

02:25.213 --> 02:27.448
Thank you for everything.

02:27.481 --> 02:30.418
- Seems like you've
all gotten close.

02:30.451 --> 02:32.453
- I'm just glad that
Sean's forgiven me.

02:32.486 --> 02:34.388
- It was a honest
mistake, Melanie.

02:34.422 --> 02:36.557
At the time,
you were sure it was him.

02:36.590 --> 02:37.625
- I was wrong.

02:37.658 --> 02:39.593
We were both wrong.

02:39.627 --> 02:41.329
- You ready to go, Mom?
- Yeah.

02:41.362 --> 02:43.464
- Last time I saw you,
you were six years old.

02:43.497 --> 02:44.965
Now you're getting married.
Congratulations.

02:44.998 --> 02:46.033
- Thank you.

02:46.066 --> 02:48.436
- We're taking Sean out
for his birthday tonight.

02:48.469 --> 02:50.571
- It's the first time
I can legally drink.

02:50.604 --> 02:53.541
- Well, have fun, and...

02:53.574 --> 02:55.343
stay safe.

02:56.510 --> 02:57.578
- Bye.

03:02.450 --> 03:04.518
- You okay with all this?
- I'm good.

03:04.552 --> 03:06.320
I'm just glad he's out of jail.

03:06.354 --> 03:08.256
- [exhales]

03:08.289 --> 03:09.457
Me too.

03:11.259 --> 03:12.226
- [sighs softly]

03:12.260 --> 03:15.329
- Thank you.
- Okay, yeah, um...

03:15.363 --> 03:18.332
[dark music]

03:18.366 --> 03:21.235
*

03:21.269 --> 03:22.703
- Detective Tutuola.

03:22.736 --> 03:24.272
- Melanie Harper asked for me?

03:24.305 --> 03:25.739
- Inside.
She's a mess.

03:25.773 --> 03:26.774
- What are we looking at?

03:26.807 --> 03:27.808
- Mother was sleeping,

03:27.841 --> 03:29.443
smelled smoke,
called it in.

03:29.477 --> 03:31.612
Girl was raped, strangled,

03:31.645 --> 03:34.548
stabbed, doused in bleach,
burned.

03:34.582 --> 03:41.289
*

03:41.322 --> 03:42.656
- Okay, Momma's here.
Momma's here, okay?

03:42.690 --> 03:44.024
Okay, it's gonna be okay.

03:44.057 --> 03:45.459
We're going to the hospital.
It's gonna be--

03:45.493 --> 03:46.527
- Melanie, what happened?

03:46.560 --> 03:47.661
- Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

03:47.695 --> 03:50.331
I came down and I--
I found her like this.

03:50.364 --> 03:52.266
- Did you see anything
or hear anybody?

03:52.300 --> 03:53.367
- Here, I'm right here.

03:53.401 --> 03:54.402
I heard a man.

03:54.435 --> 03:55.569
- Did you recognize his voice?

03:55.603 --> 03:57.305
- [panting]

03:57.338 --> 03:59.307
I think it was Sean.

03:59.340 --> 04:01.475
*

04:01.509 --> 04:02.776
- Sean Roberts?

04:02.810 --> 04:04.778
The guy we just
got out of prison?

04:04.812 --> 04:07.348
- Yeah.

04:07.381 --> 04:08.749
[siren wailing]

04:08.782 --> 04:11.251
*

04:13.387 --> 04:16.357
[dramatic music]

04:59.867 --> 05:00.668
- Ashley Harper was
raped and stabbed,

05:01.835 --> 05:03.904
and you think that Sean Roberts
is involved in this--how?

05:03.937 --> 05:06.039
- Well, Melanie said
she heard Sean's voice

05:06.073 --> 05:07.207
in the house.

05:07.240 --> 05:09.743
- Well, we know that they went
out together last night.

05:09.777 --> 05:10.911
Did you talk to him yet?

05:10.944 --> 05:12.413
- Well, considering the history,

05:12.446 --> 05:13.714
we figured we should
talk to you first.

05:13.747 --> 05:15.749
- Okay, all right.

05:15.783 --> 05:18.452
So what do we have?

05:18.486 --> 05:20.821
- Um, there's no sign
of forced entry,

05:20.854 --> 05:23.524
so Ashley probably did
know her attacker,

05:23.557 --> 05:25.426
and there's a kitchen knife
that's missing.

05:25.459 --> 05:26.960
- CSU's running the scene.

05:26.994 --> 05:29.129
Whoever did this,
they used bleach on her,

05:29.162 --> 05:30.431
they burned her--

05:30.464 --> 05:31.799
got rid of all DNA.

05:31.832 --> 05:32.800
- Who else was in her life?

05:32.833 --> 05:33.934
She just got engaged, right?

05:33.967 --> 05:35.002
- Right, we're tracking
down her fiancÃ©,

05:35.035 --> 05:36.103
and we're going
through her texts,

05:36.136 --> 05:37.538
we're going through
her social media.

05:37.571 --> 05:39.973
- Okay, so run down
every single angle.

05:40.007 --> 05:43.076
Uh, security cams in the house--
in the neighborhood.

05:43.110 --> 05:45.579
Traffic cams.
Canvass the neighbors.

05:45.613 --> 05:47.080
We need to be sure

05:47.114 --> 05:49.883
about every single
detail on this.

05:49.917 --> 05:50.951
[phone buzzing]

05:50.984 --> 05:52.586
[sighs]

05:52.620 --> 05:54.054
Okay, Carisi's here.

05:54.087 --> 05:55.389
Loop him in.

05:55.423 --> 05:56.524
Have him talk to the fiancÃ©.

05:56.557 --> 05:57.891
Rollins...

05:57.925 --> 06:00.994
Rollins, you talk to Sean.

06:01.028 --> 06:02.162
- Pulling me off the case?

06:02.195 --> 06:03.997
- No, actually,
I need to keep you on--

06:04.031 --> 06:06.166
you know, optics.

06:06.199 --> 06:08.035
- What's that mean?

06:08.068 --> 06:09.770
- If you step away
from the case,

06:09.803 --> 06:11.405
it'll look like you have a--

06:11.439 --> 06:13.173
something personal
with Sean, right?

06:13.206 --> 06:14.875
Give credibility
to his lawsuit.

06:14.908 --> 06:16.477
So just let Rollins
take the lead.

06:16.510 --> 06:18.479
- Got it.

06:18.512 --> 06:19.547
- [sighs]

06:22.149 --> 06:24.485
Ms. Harper,

06:24.518 --> 06:25.819
I'm so sorry.

06:25.853 --> 06:27.154
What did the doctors say?

06:27.187 --> 06:29.790
- She's still in surgery.

06:29.823 --> 06:31.859
She lost a lot of blood.

06:31.892 --> 06:33.126
The--the burns are--

06:33.160 --> 06:34.795
- It's okay.

06:34.828 --> 06:36.797
My detectives said that

06:36.830 --> 06:40.534
you heard Sean Roberts' voice
in your house last night?

06:40.568 --> 06:44.104
- Yes, um, he and Ashley
were talking.

06:44.137 --> 06:45.839
- Do you remember what time

06:45.873 --> 06:47.074
you heard them talking?

06:47.107 --> 06:49.443
- Um, must've been
about midnight.

06:49.477 --> 06:50.277
- Okay.

06:50.310 --> 06:51.579
- And I took a shower,
and then I--

06:51.612 --> 06:53.981
- Right.
- I went to sleep.

06:54.014 --> 06:56.116
So...have you talked to Sean?

06:56.149 --> 06:57.985
I mean, maybe he saw...

06:58.018 --> 06:59.620
- We're gonna talk to him.

06:59.653 --> 07:00.921
Listen to me.

07:00.954 --> 07:04.492
Ms. Harper, can you
think of anyone

07:04.525 --> 07:06.093
who would want to
hurt your daughter?

07:06.126 --> 07:08.161
- No.
No one.

07:08.195 --> 07:09.863
- What about the fiancÃ©?

07:09.897 --> 07:10.864
Was he at the dinner?

07:10.898 --> 07:11.932
- Zach?
No.

07:11.965 --> 07:13.867
No, he--he didn't like Sean.

07:13.901 --> 07:15.536
He and Ashley were
arguing about that, so--

07:15.569 --> 07:17.070
oh, I got to call him.

07:17.104 --> 07:18.939
[gasps]

07:18.972 --> 07:20.541
Oh...

07:20.574 --> 07:21.842
- What?

07:21.875 --> 07:23.511
- Ashley's engagement ring--

07:23.544 --> 07:26.013
it wasn't on her finger.

07:29.082 --> 07:32.019
[somber music]

07:32.052 --> 07:34.922
*

07:34.955 --> 07:37.958
[crying]

07:41.529 --> 07:42.930
[rapping on door]

07:42.963 --> 07:44.565
- Sean Roberts!

07:44.598 --> 07:46.099
*

07:46.133 --> 07:48.569
- Maybe we waited too long,
and he got spooked, ran.

07:48.602 --> 07:51.539
- This guy's got 30 million
reasons not to leave town.

07:51.572 --> 07:52.640
[locks unlatching]

07:52.673 --> 07:54.074
- Hey, Sean.

07:54.107 --> 07:55.275
Can we talk to you
for a minute?

07:55.308 --> 07:56.276
- Why?

07:56.309 --> 07:57.945
- Mind if we come inside?

07:57.978 --> 07:59.647
- Yeah, I do.

07:59.680 --> 08:02.082
What's this about?

08:02.115 --> 08:06.219
- Ashley Harper was raped
and murdered last night.

08:06.253 --> 08:07.988
- What?

08:08.021 --> 08:09.590
Oh, my God.

08:09.623 --> 08:12.593
W-what happened?

08:12.626 --> 08:14.595
Ashley's dead?

08:14.628 --> 08:17.097
Melanie must be freaking out.
I-I have to go.

08:17.130 --> 08:18.265
- Before--before you do,

08:18.298 --> 08:21.268
can we just ask you
a few questions?

08:21.301 --> 08:22.903
- You want to talk to me?

08:22.936 --> 08:25.205
You don't think that I--

08:25.238 --> 08:26.273
do I need a lawyer?

08:26.306 --> 08:27.340
- Why would you need a lawyer?

08:27.374 --> 08:29.142
- Anytime you talk to the cops,
you need a lawyer.

08:29.176 --> 08:30.310
That's what you taught me.

08:30.343 --> 08:32.145
- Were you at Ashley's
house last night?

08:32.179 --> 08:34.915
- No, we--we had
dinner together,

08:34.948 --> 08:36.149
and then she left early.

08:36.183 --> 08:37.250
- You see her after dinner?

08:37.284 --> 08:39.553
- No.
- What time did you leave?

08:39.587 --> 08:41.288
- 11:00, 11:30.

08:41.321 --> 08:43.156
- Where'd you go?

08:43.190 --> 08:44.324
- Strip club.

08:44.357 --> 08:47.160
- Is there where
you hurt your hand?

08:47.194 --> 08:48.228
- Yeah.
- Right.

08:48.261 --> 08:49.329
Did you go alone?

08:49.362 --> 08:51.131
- No, with a buddy.

08:51.164 --> 08:52.265
- Ah.
- A buddy.

08:52.299 --> 08:53.634
What kind of buddy?

08:53.667 --> 08:55.636
- A guy from the inside, okay?

08:55.669 --> 08:57.037
Jeff Nichols.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.639
Yeah, he was at
my birthday dinner.

08:58.672 --> 09:00.073
He can vouch for me.
- Great.

09:00.107 --> 09:02.042
Where can we find this Jeff?

09:02.075 --> 09:04.211
- Uh, Hell's Gate Diner.

09:05.646 --> 09:07.180
Now, if you're not
gonna arrest me,

09:07.214 --> 09:08.281
then you need to leave,

09:08.315 --> 09:10.317
because I need to call Melanie.

09:12.720 --> 09:13.687
[door closes]

09:13.721 --> 09:15.022
- Sure ain't helping himself.

09:15.055 --> 09:16.089
- Mm-mm.

09:16.123 --> 09:17.625
- Put a unmarked car
on this block

09:17.658 --> 09:19.126
in case he decides to run.

09:19.159 --> 09:21.061
- You think he really had
something to do with this?

09:21.094 --> 09:23.096
- I hope not.

09:24.231 --> 09:26.767
*

09:26.800 --> 09:28.201
Jeff Nichols?

09:28.235 --> 09:29.402
- Uh-huh.

09:29.436 --> 09:33.206
- Were you with Sean Roberts
and Ashley Harper last night?

09:33.240 --> 09:34.374
- Yeah.

09:34.407 --> 09:36.710
Yeah, after dinner,
we went to the ballet

09:36.744 --> 09:38.011
on 10th Avenue.

09:38.045 --> 09:39.813
Ask the stripper--
some Russian lesbian.

09:39.847 --> 09:41.181
We were with her
most of the night.

09:41.214 --> 09:42.650
- Sean told you to say that?

09:42.683 --> 09:44.351
- No.
- Listen.

09:44.384 --> 09:46.386
Ashley Harper was murdered
last night,

09:46.419 --> 09:48.055
so you're gonna need
to come clean.

09:48.088 --> 09:49.757
- I am.
I swear.

09:49.790 --> 09:51.124
- Listen, dude.

09:51.158 --> 09:53.360
You're on parole.

09:53.393 --> 09:54.662
Don't lie to me.

09:54.695 --> 09:57.698
I'll throw your ass
back in prison.

10:01.068 --> 10:03.103
- Okay.
Okay.

10:03.136 --> 10:06.239
Sean just called me--
begged me to vouch for him.

10:06.273 --> 10:07.808
Said you guys were
jamming him up

10:07.841 --> 10:09.777
just like last time.

10:09.810 --> 10:11.144
- Did he even come
to the club?

10:11.178 --> 10:12.212
- Yeah.
[sighs]

10:12.245 --> 10:14.114
But he came late--
about 2:00.

10:14.147 --> 10:15.182
- Okay.

10:15.215 --> 10:17.751
Uh, did you notice
a cut on his hand?

10:17.785 --> 10:18.819
- I don't remember.

10:18.852 --> 10:21.689
Look, all I know is,
Sean would never hurt that girl.

10:21.722 --> 10:22.656
He adored her.

10:22.690 --> 10:24.725
All night, he was a shoulder
for her to cry on.

10:24.758 --> 10:25.859
- Why was she crying?

10:25.893 --> 10:27.194
- Her fiancÃ©.

10:27.227 --> 10:28.295
She, she--I don't know.

10:28.328 --> 10:31.631
He was, like, threatening
to break off the engagement.

10:33.867 --> 10:36.136
- I can't believe
Ashley's really...

10:38.806 --> 10:41.208
What, uh...

10:41.241 --> 10:42.843
what happened?

10:42.876 --> 10:43.844
- We're not sure.

10:43.877 --> 10:45.846
We were hoping you could
help us out with that.

10:45.879 --> 10:47.114
- What are you talking about?

10:47.147 --> 10:50.283
- When was the last time
you saw Ashley?

10:50.317 --> 10:52.753
- Yesterday, before she went
to dinner with that convict.

10:52.786 --> 10:54.454
- Sean Roberts.

10:54.487 --> 10:56.857
Let me ask, were you and Ashley

10:56.890 --> 10:58.759
fighting about him?

10:58.792 --> 10:59.760
- What?
No.

10:59.793 --> 11:01.795
- Ah, wrong answer.

11:01.829 --> 11:04.698
- 'Cause you sent
half a dozen texts.

11:04.732 --> 11:07.167
7:10, "It's over."

11:07.200 --> 11:09.469
7:30, "I want my ring back."

11:09.502 --> 11:11.238
8:00, "I'm gonna get that ring."

11:11.271 --> 11:12.239
Should I go on?
- No.

11:12.272 --> 11:13.206
- Come on, you must have known

11:13.240 --> 11:14.908
we were going to look through
Ashley's phone.

11:14.942 --> 11:16.209
You see, when you lie to us,

11:16.243 --> 11:18.078
it makes us curious.

11:18.111 --> 11:21.114
- I was pissed.

11:21.148 --> 11:22.215
We made plans last night,

11:22.249 --> 11:26.119
and she blew me off
for that guy Sean.

11:26.153 --> 11:26.954
I get it.

11:26.987 --> 11:29.857
He spent 16 years
in prison, but--

11:29.890 --> 11:32.292
and he was innocent, but that
doesn't make him a saint.

11:32.325 --> 11:33.326
- Well, that's fair enough,

11:33.360 --> 11:34.762
but where were you last night--

11:34.795 --> 11:37.197
after midnight?

11:37.230 --> 11:38.866
- I was at a bar--
Dakota Bar.

11:38.899 --> 11:40.133
- The Dakota Bar.

11:40.167 --> 11:42.169
That's two blocks
from Ashley's house.

11:42.202 --> 11:43.370
- And my apartment.

11:43.403 --> 11:44.304
Ask the bartender.

11:44.337 --> 11:46.239
I was there from midnight
until closing.

11:46.273 --> 11:47.407
- You were there
the entire time?

11:47.440 --> 11:51.278
Four solid hours at the bar?

11:51.311 --> 11:52.479
- No.
- No?

11:52.512 --> 11:54.748
- Some girl spilled
red wine on my shirt.

11:54.782 --> 11:56.850
I went home to change.
Then I went back to the bar.

11:56.884 --> 12:00.120
- Oh, that's very
convenient for you.

12:00.153 --> 12:02.122
- I didn't kill Ashley.

12:02.155 --> 12:03.356
*

12:03.390 --> 12:05.759
Are you--are you guys crazy?

12:05.793 --> 12:08.762
I have nothing
to do with this.

12:08.796 --> 12:10.497
- As of now,
who is our main suspect,

12:10.530 --> 12:11.765
Sean or Zach?

12:11.799 --> 12:13.901
- As of now?
Both.

12:13.934 --> 12:15.869
- Or an unknown.

12:15.903 --> 12:18.238
I've been searching through
Ashley's social media.

12:18.271 --> 12:20.173
She's got a lot
of male followers.

12:20.207 --> 12:21.241
- Okay, okay, so let's, uh...

12:21.274 --> 12:22.242
What do we have on Sean?

12:22.275 --> 12:23.510
- So, the timeline is tight.

12:23.543 --> 12:26.146
Ashley was attacked
sometime between midnight,

12:26.179 --> 12:27.848
when Melanie heard her voice--

12:27.881 --> 12:29.349
- And Sean's voice.

12:29.382 --> 12:31.551
- And 1:20,
when Melanie called 911.

12:31.584 --> 12:33.553
