would be able to live a normal,
law-abiding life upon release?

24:22.995 --> 24:25.532
- Unfortunately,
it's almost impossible.

24:25.565 --> 24:26.933
- Thank you.

24:26.966 --> 24:28.968
Nothing further.

24:31.771 --> 24:33.806
- Have you ever
met Sean Roberts?

24:33.840 --> 24:34.841
- No.

24:34.874 --> 24:36.609
- So your expert opinions

24:36.643 --> 24:37.977
don't apply to him specifically,

24:38.010 --> 24:39.579
do they?

24:39.612 --> 24:42.949
They're based on
other exonerees.

24:42.982 --> 24:43.950
- That's right.

24:43.983 --> 24:45.284
- So what you're saying is,

24:45.317 --> 24:47.787
your testimony is totally
irrelevant to Sean

24:47.820 --> 24:49.021
and a complete waste of time?

24:49.055 --> 24:52.024
- Objection.
- Sustained.

24:52.058 --> 24:54.694
- Nothing further.

24:54.727 --> 24:57.697
[tense music]

24:57.730 --> 25:00.299
*

25:00.332 --> 25:01.701
- Counselor,

25:01.734 --> 25:03.302
where would you
like your witness?

25:03.335 --> 25:04.737
- How are you, Charlie?

25:04.771 --> 25:05.972
- Nervous.
- All right.

25:06.005 --> 25:07.574
Ah, you'll be fine.

25:07.607 --> 25:08.875
Go have a seat over there.
I'll be right with you.

25:08.908 --> 25:09.909
- Right there.

25:12.044 --> 25:13.045
- How's he really doing?

25:13.079 --> 25:14.947
- He's okay.
A little jittery.

25:14.981 --> 25:17.550
- The thing is, he's--
he's not the brightest bulb,

25:17.584 --> 25:20.019
but if you--
if you take it easy with him,

25:20.052 --> 25:22.054
he'll calm down.

25:23.322 --> 25:24.490
- You haven't been
in the gallery.

25:24.523 --> 25:27.326
- Just in case you change
your mind and decide to call me.

25:27.359 --> 25:28.728
- You get why I can't, right?

25:28.761 --> 25:30.763
- Well, I get why
you think you can't.

25:30.797 --> 25:33.700
The DA put Sean away
for 16 years, not me.

25:33.733 --> 25:34.834
I did my job.

25:34.867 --> 25:35.935
I did it right then.

25:35.968 --> 25:37.069
I did it right this time, too.

25:37.103 --> 25:38.137
- I know.

25:38.170 --> 25:40.840
- I just want you to know,
I have nothing to hide.

25:40.873 --> 25:42.642
- I believe you.

25:42.675 --> 25:44.744
- Doesn't seem that way.

25:47.914 --> 25:50.617
- My girlfriend and I
had just had sex

25:50.650 --> 25:51.751
on the roof,

25:51.784 --> 25:53.986
and that's when I
saw Sean Roberts

25:54.020 --> 25:57.957
leave the house and toss
something in the trash.

25:57.990 --> 25:59.759
- What time was this?

25:59.792 --> 26:00.927
- 1:15.

26:00.960 --> 26:02.662
- Then what happened?

26:02.695 --> 26:05.064
- I went to see what he tossed.

26:05.097 --> 26:06.633
It was a knife.

26:06.666 --> 26:07.934
I picked it up.

26:07.967 --> 26:11.037
- You saw Sean Roberts leave
the Harper residence

26:11.070 --> 26:13.906
at 1:15 and throw
a knife in the trash?

26:13.940 --> 26:15.341
- Yes.

26:15.374 --> 26:16.643
- Okay.

26:16.676 --> 26:17.777
The knife has been
previously entered

26:17.810 --> 26:21.147
as People's Exhibit A.

26:21.180 --> 26:23.683
The same knife has been
determined to have

26:23.716 --> 26:25.785
Ashley's blood on it.

26:32.091 --> 26:34.160
- Hello, Charlie.

26:34.193 --> 26:37.864
So, you had a fun time on
the roof with your girlfriend.

26:37.897 --> 26:39.165
Lucky you.

26:39.198 --> 26:40.933
Can I ask you something?

26:40.967 --> 26:44.837
Had you been smoking pot
or drinking alcohol?

26:46.005 --> 26:48.074
- [laughs]
We smoked a little weed.

26:48.107 --> 26:50.142
- So, high on marijuana,

26:50.176 --> 26:52.812
through the black of night
at 1:15 in the morning,

26:52.845 --> 26:54.647
you're absolutely positive

26:54.681 --> 26:57.750
you saw Sean Roberts
down on the street?

26:57.784 --> 26:58.951
- I think so.

26:58.985 --> 27:00.419
It looked like him.

27:00.452 --> 27:03.690
Plus, Detective Rollins, uh--

27:03.723 --> 27:06.225
uh, yeah, I'm positive.

27:06.258 --> 27:08.895
- Plus Detective Rollins?

27:08.928 --> 27:11.998
Did she tell you
to say something?

27:12.031 --> 27:13.966
- No, not really.

27:14.000 --> 27:16.102
I said I thought
I saw Sean's face.

27:16.135 --> 27:19.872
- And she encouraged you
to say it was Sean?

27:19.906 --> 27:22.675
Maybe she nodded or smiled.

27:22.709 --> 27:25.144
- She patted me
on the shoulder

27:25.177 --> 27:27.747
and told me it was okay.

27:27.780 --> 27:29.749
I thought she wanted me
to say it was him.

27:29.782 --> 27:33.820
- Did she help you figure out
what time you saw him, too?

27:33.853 --> 27:34.821
*

27:34.854 --> 27:35.988
- I guess.

27:36.022 --> 27:37.724
I-I...

27:37.757 --> 27:40.192
I wasn't sure if I saw Sean

27:40.226 --> 27:43.429
leave before or after
Shyvon and I had sex.

27:43.462 --> 27:45.064
But she--
- She what?

27:45.097 --> 27:46.432
- Sh--

27:46.465 --> 27:48.768
*

27:48.801 --> 27:50.002
Sh--

27:50.036 --> 27:52.805
*

27:52.839 --> 27:54.741
- I know she's attractive.

27:54.774 --> 27:58.144
But don't look to her for help.

27:58.177 --> 27:59.946
Look at me, Charlie.

27:59.979 --> 28:02.481
Why did you say what you did?

28:02.514 --> 28:04.116
*

28:04.150 --> 28:07.186
- I thought she would like it
if I said after.

28:07.219 --> 28:08.020
And she was really nice.

28:08.054 --> 28:11.457
- So Detective Rollins
encouraged you--

28:11.490 --> 28:12.491
flirted with you--

28:12.524 --> 28:14.493
to say you had seen Sean Roberts

28:14.526 --> 28:16.829
leave Ashley's home at 1:15?

28:16.863 --> 28:18.164
- Objection: Mr. Buchanan
is putting words

28:18.197 --> 28:19.165
in this witness's mouth.

28:19.198 --> 28:21.300
- Overruled.
Answer the question.

28:21.333 --> 28:22.769
- No.

28:22.802 --> 28:25.104
I just wanted her to like me.

28:25.137 --> 28:27.907
And she needed to
solve her case.

28:27.940 --> 28:29.475
- So Detective Rollins
encouraged you

28:29.508 --> 28:31.010
to see Sean Roberts,

28:31.043 --> 28:33.212
then you made her happy
by saying you had seen him

28:33.245 --> 28:35.014
at 1:15 exactly?

28:35.047 --> 28:37.316
- That's a good way
of saying it.

28:37.349 --> 28:38.985
- [scoffs]

28:39.018 --> 28:43.489
*

28:43.522 --> 28:45.491
Nothing further.

28:56.402 --> 28:57.369
- We got a guy on trial
who was wrongfully convicted

28:58.004 --> 28:58.871
on bad eyewitness testimony,

28:58.905 --> 29:01.207
and you don't tell me
that the kid waffled

29:01.240 --> 29:02.341
on the ID or the time.

29:02.374 --> 29:03.475
- He waffled.
He did not lie.

29:03.509 --> 29:05.044
There is a big difference.

29:05.077 --> 29:06.178
- Now you're parsing
degrees of deceit.

29:06.212 --> 29:07.814
- Listen,
Buchanan is gonna turn this

29:07.847 --> 29:09.415
into you manipulating the kid

29:09.448 --> 29:10.416
to defend Fin.

29:10.449 --> 29:11.984
- Charlie's telling the truth.

29:12.018 --> 29:14.186
He saw Sean leave the house,

29:14.220 --> 29:16.823
toss the knife after he
and his girlfriend had sex,

29:16.856 --> 29:19.158
which was around 1:15 or so.
That's the truth.

29:19.191 --> 29:21.127
I can't help it if the kid
has a crush on me, or--

29:21.160 --> 29:22.228
- Hold on, so you were aware

29:22.261 --> 29:23.395
that he had an affection
for you--

29:23.429 --> 29:25.131
that he had a desire
to make you happy?

29:25.164 --> 29:26.365
- Lieutenant, listen.
I was there, all right?

29:26.398 --> 29:27.599
Rollins didn't lead him.

29:27.633 --> 29:29.468
- Don't make excuses for her.
That's not what the jury thinks.

29:29.501 --> 29:31.003
- Oh, come on.
You know what, Counselor?

29:31.037 --> 29:32.271
It's not Rollins's fault

29:32.304 --> 29:34.106
that Buchanan spun
that kid upside-down

29:34.140 --> 29:35.207
and you didn't know
how to stop him.

29:35.241 --> 29:37.009
- Okay, thank you.
We're done.

29:44.250 --> 29:46.085
- [sighs]

29:46.118 --> 29:47.286
- Okay.

29:47.319 --> 29:49.521
So where do we go
from here?

29:49.555 --> 29:52.091
- They're not gonna convict
on Charlie's testimony.

29:52.124 --> 29:54.126
Not anymore.

29:54.160 --> 29:56.562
We need to double down
on the physical evidence.

29:56.595 --> 29:59.498
- How do we do that?

30:03.102 --> 30:05.872
- I entered the defendant's
apartment with several officers

30:05.905 --> 30:07.406
and we began a search.

30:07.439 --> 30:08.607
I looked in the sink.

30:08.640 --> 30:10.376
I stuck a pencil in the drain

30:10.409 --> 30:12.178
and pulled out the diamond ring.

30:12.211 --> 30:13.312
- How many of
the police officers

30:13.345 --> 30:14.413
were present at that time?

30:14.446 --> 30:16.515
- At any given time, six to ten.

30:16.548 --> 30:17.549
- Okay.

30:17.583 --> 30:21.087
Detective Tutuola, um...

30:21.120 --> 30:22.421
how do you know
Sean Roberts?

30:22.454 --> 30:24.891
- I arrested him for rape
16 years ago.

30:24.924 --> 30:26.292
- He was found innocent
of that crime

30:26.325 --> 30:28.494
and released from prison
a month ago.

30:28.527 --> 30:30.129
Does that bother you?

30:30.162 --> 30:31.297
- Sure it does.

30:31.330 --> 30:33.432
But we went with
the evidence we had.

30:33.465 --> 30:35.167
- Do you have, um, any kind of--

30:35.201 --> 30:37.203
I don't know--grudge, vendetta

30:37.236 --> 30:38.570
against the defendant?

30:38.604 --> 30:39.906
- I do now he killed Ash.

30:39.939 --> 30:42.108
- Objection!
- Sustained.

30:42.141 --> 30:44.610
Please refrain from drawing
conclusions, Detective.

30:44.643 --> 30:45.878
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

30:45.912 --> 30:47.446
I mean, honestly,

30:47.479 --> 30:49.315
I have no grudges
against the man.

30:49.348 --> 30:50.917
If anything,
I was rooting for him

30:50.950 --> 30:53.152
when he got out.

30:53.185 --> 30:55.087
- Thank you.
Nothing further.

30:57.156 --> 30:59.458
- You must be embarrassed about
putting an innocent man

30:59.491 --> 31:01.360
in prison for 16 years.

31:01.393 --> 31:02.594
- I didn't put him there.

31:02.628 --> 31:04.196
I just arrested him.

31:04.230 --> 31:05.464
And no, I'm not embarrassed.

31:05.497 --> 31:06.632
I just did my job.

31:06.665 --> 31:07.466
- You say
you're not embarrassed,

31:07.499 --> 31:10.669
even though convicting
an innocent man

31:10.702 --> 31:14.106
obviously reflects poorly on you
as a police officer.

31:14.140 --> 31:15.607
Your job is to arrest
guilty people,

31:15.641 --> 31:16.642
not innocent ones.

31:16.675 --> 31:18.110
- That's correct.

31:18.144 --> 31:19.478
But it doesn't always
go that way.

31:19.511 --> 31:20.913
That's just the way it is.

31:20.947 --> 31:22.348
- Right.

31:22.381 --> 31:24.116
It's just the way it is.

31:24.150 --> 31:26.185
So given what's transpired,

31:26.218 --> 31:28.254
you'd obviously feel
better about yourself,

31:28.287 --> 31:30.622
your reputation,
the department's reputation,

31:30.656 --> 31:34.326
if Sean was found guilty
of this crime, right?

31:34.360 --> 31:35.627
It would be vindication.

31:35.661 --> 31:38.430
You've buried an innocent man,

31:38.464 --> 31:40.366
but that's no big deal,

31:40.399 --> 31:41.467
because he's a criminal.

31:41.500 --> 31:44.270
- And like I said before,
I did my job right then

31:44.303 --> 31:45.271
and now.

31:45.304 --> 31:46.505
- By doing your job right,

31:46.538 --> 31:49.475
do you mean framing
Sean Roberts again?

31:49.508 --> 31:51.978
- Objection!

31:52.011 --> 31:53.445
- Withdrawn.

31:53.479 --> 31:56.448
[tense music]

31:56.482 --> 31:59.485
*

32:00.987 --> 32:02.354
- How'd it go?

32:02.388 --> 32:04.423
- [sighs]
As well as it could have.

32:04.456 --> 32:07.293
Jury looks at a guy
who was put away innocent,

32:07.326 --> 32:08.294
they hesitate.

32:08.327 --> 32:09.361
- They should.

32:09.395 --> 32:10.529
- Not this time, Melanie.

32:10.562 --> 32:12.664
He's guilty.
There's no question about this.

32:12.698 --> 32:16.235
- No, but that's what
you said last time.

32:16.268 --> 32:18.237
None of us saw
what happened.

32:18.270 --> 32:19.438
I mean, if you really
think about it, I mean,

32:19.471 --> 32:21.240
we're all just--
we're just guessing.

32:21.273 --> 32:23.375
We're just filling
in the blanks and--

32:23.409 --> 32:24.610
and connecting the dots.

32:24.643 --> 32:27.246
- I found Ashley's
ring in his drain.

32:27.279 --> 32:28.547
How else could it
have gotten there?

32:28.580 --> 32:30.316
- According to Sean's lawyer--

32:30.349 --> 32:32.418
- I did not plant
that ring, okay?

32:32.451 --> 32:33.552
Why would I?

32:33.585 --> 32:36.355
Think about it.

32:36.388 --> 32:38.424
- I'm sorry, I'm just--

32:38.457 --> 32:40.392
I was just--
I was so sure last time,

32:40.426 --> 32:43.462
and then I was wrong,
and I just--

32:43.495 --> 32:46.332
I just can't trust myself.

32:46.365 --> 32:49.001
- Did you hear Sean and Ashley
speaking that night?

32:49.035 --> 32:51.003
Yes or no?

32:51.037 --> 32:53.239
*

32:53.272 --> 32:54.306
- I'm not sure now.

32:54.340 --> 32:55.541
- That's not
what you told me

32:55.574 --> 32:57.409
that night
at the crime scene.

32:57.443 --> 32:59.578
No one's asking you
to say if he's guilty.

32:59.611 --> 33:02.781
That's the jury's job,
not yours.

33:02.814 --> 33:06.052
- He already served 16 years.

33:06.085 --> 33:08.620
What if I'm wrong again?

33:08.654 --> 33:11.590
*

33:11.623 --> 33:12.724
- What do you mean,
she won't testify?

33:12.758 --> 33:15.594
- She told me she's not sure
she heard Sean's voice--

33:15.627 --> 33:17.263
not anymore.

33:17.296 --> 33:18.464
- What the hell did
you say to her?

33:18.497 --> 33:19.298
- You putting this on me?

33:19.331 --> 33:21.033
- You're the last person
she talked to.

33:21.067 --> 33:22.468
- Hold on.

33:22.501 --> 33:23.702
Fin was trying to help.

33:23.735 --> 33:26.738
It's not his fault
that she got cold feet.

33:26.772 --> 33:28.507
- I feel for her.
I really do.

33:28.540 --> 33:30.276
But she needs to testify.

33:30.309 --> 33:31.277
After the Charlie debacle,

33:31.310 --> 33:33.345
she's the only one who can
put Sean at the scene.

33:33.379 --> 33:34.346
- She won't cooperate.

33:34.380 --> 33:36.482
- Then I'll have to call her
as a hostile witness

33:36.515 --> 33:38.784
and compel her testimony.

33:38.817 --> 33:40.086
- [sighs]
- Look, guys.

33:40.119 --> 33:41.587
This isn't about Melanie.

33:41.620 --> 33:43.389
It's about her daughter.

33:43.422 --> 33:46.258
We need to get justice for her--

33:46.292 --> 33:49.261
with or without cooperation.

33:56.368 --> 33:57.169
- I told you,
I don't want to do this.

33:57.936 --> 33:59.271
- Permission to treat
the witness

33:59.305 --> 34:00.272
as hostile, Your Honor?

34:00.306 --> 34:01.173
- Permission granted.
Proceed.

34:01.207 --> 34:03.442
You must answer the questions,
Ms. Harper.

34:05.544 --> 34:09.081
- The night of your daughter's
rape and murder,

34:09.115 --> 34:11.183
you heard the defendant's
voice in your house.

34:11.217 --> 34:14.353
He was talking to Ashley
around midnight.

34:14.386 --> 34:15.687
He was talking to Ashley
around midnight--

34:15.721 --> 34:17.256
I can show you
the police report

34:17.289 --> 34:18.324
to help refresh your memory.

34:18.357 --> 34:19.358
- Okay, okay, yes.

34:19.391 --> 34:21.427
I...

34:21.460 --> 34:22.561
I heard Sean's voice.

34:22.594 --> 34:25.164
I...well, I thought
I did, anyway.

34:25.197 --> 34:26.265
I'm--I'm not sure now.

34:26.298 --> 34:29.401
- You were sure then--
sure enough to tell the police.

34:30.402 --> 34:33.305
- I don't think that Sean

34:33.339 --> 34:35.207
would kill Ashley.

34:35.241 --> 34:37.443
He cared about her.

34:37.476 --> 34:38.644
He had his whole future
ahead of him.

34:38.677 --> 34:40.546
- And yet you said
you heard his voice

34:40.579 --> 34:42.581
in your house the night
of the murder.

34:42.614 --> 34:43.682
- Well, yes, I said that, but--

34:43.715 --> 34:45.151
- But you didn't hear him leave,

34:45.184 --> 34:46.552
and you didn't hear
anyone else come in.

34:46.585 --> 34:49.555
- No, but that's what
I thought last time,

34:49.588 --> 34:52.458
and I was wrong.

34:52.491 --> 34:56.262
What I did to Sean
was unforgivable.

34:57.396 --> 34:59.165
I told the jury he did it.

34:59.198 --> 35:01.500
I pointed at him,
and I said,

35:01.533 --> 35:03.502
"That's the man who raped me."

35:03.535 --> 35:05.204
And I was wrong.

35:05.237 --> 35:06.705
- That's why you're hesitant
to identify him now--

35:06.738 --> 35:08.374
because if you were wrong then,

35:08.407 --> 35:09.608
you might be wrong again now.

35:09.641 --> 35:11.410
- If Sean was there,
then that would mean--

35:11.443 --> 35:12.478
- That means he killed her.

35:12.511 --> 35:13.479
Is that what you
were about to say?

35:13.512 --> 35:15.414
- Objection!
- Let me rephrase.

35:15.447 --> 35:18.284
Ms. Harper, you blame yourself

35:18.317 --> 35:20.152
for your daughter's death,
don't you?

35:20.186 --> 35:21.420
- Excuse me?

35:21.453 --> 35:25.224
- You caused Ashley's death.

35:25.257 --> 35:26.425
[tense music]

35:26.458 --> 35:28.560
You sent him to prison,

35:28.594 --> 35:31.363
where he was victimized
and abused for 16 years.

35:31.397 --> 35:34.666
Thanks to you, he learned how
to become a killer and a rapist.

35:34.700 --> 35:37.369
- Objection--is there
a question anywhere here?

35:37.403 --> 35:38.437
- Get to the point, Mr. Barba.

35:38.470 --> 35:40.372
- The point is, if you had not

35:40.406 --> 35:41.607
made that false identification

35:41.640 --> 35:43.342
16 years ago,

35:43.375 --> 35:45.177
he never would've
gone to prison,

35:45.211 --> 35:47.379
which means he never
would've killed Ashley.

35:47.413 --> 35:48.447
- That's not true.

35:48.480 --> 35:50.249
- That's not true, or you don't
want it to be true?

35:50.282 --> 35:51.550
Because, in your mind,

35:51.583 --> 35:53.252
if he killed Ashley,

35:53.285 --> 35:55.554
you killed her.

35:55.587 --> 35:57.789
And that's too
painful to accept.

35:57.823 --> 36:00.392
*

36:00.426 --> 36:03.395
That's why you don't
want to testify.

36:03.429 --> 36:10.436
*

36:12.771 --> 36:14.773
- [crying]

36:16.675 --> 36:18.644
I-I sent him there.

36:18.677 --> 36:21.380
*

36:21.413 --> 36:24.283
Every time he was

36:24.316 --> 36:27.753
beaten or raped,

36:27.786 --> 36:30.522
it was my fault.

36:30.556 --> 36:32.324
I turned him into a rapist--

36:32.358 --> 36:35.627
a monster.

36:35.661 --> 36:38.697
And it was my fault.

36:38.730 --> 36:41.700
I'm the--
I'm the guilty one here.

36:41.733 --> 36:46.505
*

36:46.538 --> 36:49.608
- To feel this guilty,

36:49.641 --> 36:53.712
you obviously believe
he killed your daughter.

36:53.745 --> 36:56.315
Which means you are certain

36:56.348 --> 36:58.317
you heard Sean's voice
in your house

36:58.350 --> 37:01.019
the night of the murder,
around midnight.

37:01.052 --> 37:03.322
Correct?

37:03.355 --> 37:08.327
*

37:08.360 --> 37:10.329
- Yes.

37:10.362 --> 37:17.436
*

37:29.348 --> 37:32.484
- Unpleasant and tragic,
but well done.

37:32.518 --> 37:35.754
- Let's hope the jury
thinks so, too.

37:35.787 --> 37:38.657
- Looks like Buchanan
got the message.

37:39.658 --> 37:40.626
- Mr. Barba?

37:40.659 --> 37:41.727
- Mm-hmm?

37:41.760 --> 37:43.862
- I am open to
discussing a plea.

37:43.895 --> 37:45.864
- It's too late.

37:45.897 --> 37:48.900
- We'll plead guilty
to manslaughter.

37:48.934 --> 37:51.570
- He serves five years

37:51.603 --> 37:52.871
for a brutal rape and murder?

37:52.904 --> 37:53.872
Don't waste my time.

37:53.905 --> 37:55.741
- Wasted time?

37:55.774 --> 37:57.509
Ask Sean about that.

37:57.543 --> 37:58.777
16 years of it.

37:58.810 --> 38:01.480
If he serves five,
that's 21 years.

38:03.482 --> 38:06.485
You want to roll the dice
with the jury, go ahead.

38:09.921 --> 38:11.857
- Murder two.

38:11.890 --> 38:15.727
He serves a minimum of 15 years.

38:15.761 --> 38:19.097
- Done.
- And he allocutes.

38:19.130 --> 38:23.402
Everybody needs to know that
we got it right this time.

38:23.435 --> 38:26.405
[somber music]

38:26.438 --> 38:30.476
*

38:30.509 --> 38:32.544
- Sean Roberts,
your lawyer tells me

38:32.578 --> 38:33.812
you'd like to plead guilty.

38:33.845 --> 38:36.782
Is that correct?

38:36.815 --> 38:37.916
- Yes, Your Honor.

38:37.949 --> 38:39.685
- Do you make this
plea knowingly

38:39.718 --> 38:41.687
and voluntarily?

38:41.720 --> 38:43.789
*

38:43.822 --> 38:44.790
- I do.

38:44.823 --> 38:45.891
- Has anyone induced you

38:45.924 --> 38:47.759
or coerced you in any way

38:47.793 --> 38:50.462
into pleading guilty?

38:50.496 --> 38:51.497
- No, Your Honor.

38:51.530 --> 38:56.134
- I understand you'd
like to make a statement.

38:56.167 --> 38:58.136
Proceed.

38:58.169 --> 39:04.976
*

39:05.010 --> 39:06.745
- Melanie...

39:09.915 --> 39:12.884
I'm so, so sorry.

39:12.918 --> 39:14.453
*

39:14.486 --> 39:17.689
I know how much
you loved Ashley.

39:17.723 --> 39:19.558
*

39:19.591 --> 39:22.428
But I cared about her, too.

39:22.461 --> 39:24.730
*

39:24.763 --> 39:27.999
She gave me hope
I could start over.

39:28.033 --> 39:29.935
She wasn't afraid

39:29.968 --> 39:32.638
to be alone with me.

39:32.671 --> 39:34.740
She didn't look at me
like I was dirt,

39:34.773 --> 39:38.477
like everyone else.

39:38.510 --> 39:41.747
Then that night, I was drunk.

39:41.780 --> 39:43.615
*

39:43.649 --> 39:45.517
I wasn't used to that.

39:45.551 --> 39:48.420
I went over there
to talk to her,

39:48.454 --> 39:50.422
to say I was sorry

39:50.456 --> 39:52.858
for how I acted at dinner.

39:52.891 --> 39:54.593
*

39:54.626 --> 39:58.597
And I told her how much
I liked her...

39:58.630 --> 40:02.868
*

40:02.901 --> 40:05.871
And she just sort of laughed.

40:05.904 --> 40:10.609
*

40:10.642 --> 40:12.611
And that was it.

40:12.644 --> 40:15.814
- [crying softly]

40:15.847 --> 40:19.217
- You can't let people
laugh at you.

40:19.250 --> 40:23.489
16 years, that's what I learned.

40:23.522 --> 40:26.925
Things happened to me
in prison...

40:26.958 --> 40:30.028
things I swore
I'd never do to anyone else--

40:30.061 --> 40:32.498
I ended up doing to Ashley.

40:32.531 --> 40:36.568
I didn't want to do it.

40:36.602 --> 40:38.670
It just happened.

40:38.704 --> 40:45.711
*

40:55.887 --> 40:57.455
- Melanie.

41:00.759 --> 41:03.729
I'm sorry.

41:03.762 --> 41:04.996
- I know.

41:09.067 --> 41:13.972
At least I know
he did it this time.

41:14.005 --> 41:17.543
- It's not your fault.

41:17.576 --> 41:20.712
- Then whose is it?

41:20.746 --> 41:27.753
*

41:40.599 --> 41:41.833
- How are you?

41:41.867 --> 41:44.035
- I'm good.

41:44.069 --> 41:47.639
Bad guy went down.
That's all that matters.

41:48.907 --> 41:51.877
- Well, if you ever
feel like talking...

41:51.910 --> 41:54.045
- Talking's overrated.

41:56.047 --> 41:59.618
- Justice sure isn't
pretty some days.

41:59.651 --> 42:02.921
- Damn ugly this time.

42:02.954 --> 42:06.658
*
